post_text:
Reminders for school on Monday, September 14:

We must have a signed waiver for your child to come on campus. If your child rides the bus we also need a signed Transportation Rules form returned. These waivers will be delivered today during lunch. Students will need to have these signed on Monday in order to ride the bus or come on campus.

No backpacks will be allowed this year. Students will need to bring the Chromebook to school. We have ordered plastic tote bags and a zippered pouch for each student who attends school. The Chromebook and charger needs to come to school each day and will then go home for homework.

Uniform shirts, a solid colored polo shirt, are required.

Any questions, please call the office at 785-3311.

We are so excited to see everyone!

post_text:
Students and Parents,

Just a quick update – yesterday, the WES Board of Education decided to keep July 27th as the date to begin virtual instruction for all students enrolled at Wellton Elementary School. On campus instruction will resume on August 17, 2020 unless Governor Ducey issues another executive order delaying the start of on campus instruction.

Teachers and all other staff will return to work on Monday, July 20th and we will organize parent meetings and times in which Chromebooks may be picked up for online instruction. We have been calling families to ask if students need a Chromebook, if you have internet service, and if students will be attending school when we are allowed to open. If we have not been able to reach you, please call us at 785-3311.

The Administration and staff of WES share your concerns about the safety of students and staff during the school year. We are working on getting everything ready and will take all precautions possible to ensure the safety of everyone on campus when school begins.

We will get through this pandemic together and come out stronger!

Preventive Illness Measures

Wash your hands often, and avoid touching your eyes, nose or mouth with unwashed hands.
Avoid close contact with people who are sick.
When you sneeze or cough, cover your nose, and mouth preferably into your arm/elbow, to prevent the spread of germs.
Regularly clean and disinfect surfaces and objects, such as your phone or shared workstation that could be contaminated with germs after use.
If you have cold-like symptoms, please remain at home while sick as a courtesy to others.
Practice healthy habits by aiming for the recommended eight hours of sleep, drinking plenty of fluids, and eating a well-balanced diet.
Avoid sharing food or drinks.

The above tips are your best strategy for avoiding the flu and other illnesses this season and for preventing the spread of any illness you may contact.

Measures We Will Take

All areas of the school, including buses, will be disinfected before students and staff are allowed to come back to campus.
